item.dc:creator: @brandonscarinfo brandonscarinfo
item.description:
@brandonscarinfo wrote:

make sure it is set to go to the correct path…by that I mean make sure its going to where your jdk is, I believe windows 7 has a different path than that of vista and windows 64 and windows 32

hope i helped

also make sure that you have changed the jdk version to be 23 if that is what you have.
